Rendered as Claude Code over the anthropic dialect, +27 tokens vs the raw API request.
Source: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks — "MCP tools follow the naming pattern
        `mcp__<server>__<tool>`"
Not established: whether the description or input schema is rewritten, and what
                 system-prompt framing is added — Claude Code is closed-source, so only the
                 name format is citable. The token delta therefore covers only the
                 transformation above — treat it as a lower bound, not this client's full
                 cost.
No API key is needed or used: context computes this locally and sends nothing to any
provider.
Server instructions are shown for reference but are not in the request body: `jig
bench` sends only the system prompt + tools.
~approx — counted with the o200k_base tokenizer as a proxy (Claude's tokenizer is not publicly available); use --exact-anthropic for the exact total
